JAX-RPC API

Java Web Services Developer Pack 2.0, 
http://java.sun.com/webservices/jwsdp/index.jsp

Java web services:
http://java.sun.com/webservices/downloads/install-unix.html

sh jwsdp-2_0-unix.sh

----

For standalone Java(TM) applications to work with the Java(TM) Web Services Developer Pack 2.0, the JAXP classes built into JDK 1.5.x must be overridden.  Overriding these classes is not necessary in order to run the Web container or the samples, since the provided scripts set "java.endorsed.dirs".

For JDK 1.5.x users, set the java.endorsed.dirs system property to:

/afs/csail.mit.edu/u/m/mernst/java/jwsdp-2.0/jaxp/lib:/afs/csail.mit.edu/u/m/mernst/java/jwsdp-2.0/jaxp/lib/endorsed

Alternatively, create the directory:

  <JAVA_HOME>/jre/lib/endorsed

and then copy the files in the following directories to the newly created directory.

  /afs/csail.mit.edu/u/m/mernst/java/jwsdp-2.0/jaxp/lib
  /afs/csail.mit.edu/u/m/mernst/java/jwsdp-2.0/jaxp/lib/endorsed

Getting started:
/afs/csail.mit.edu/u/m/mernst/java/jwsdp-2.0/docs/GettingStarted.html

Template Build File for Web Service Clients
file:///afs/csail.mit.edu/u/m/mernst/java/jwsdp-2.0/docs/webserviceclient.html

Developing an Amazon Web Services Client
